title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1990-09-12
description: Mississippi Half Step> Walkin' Blues, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle> Big River, High Time, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Althea, Let it Grow Iko Iko, Playin' in the Band> Crazy Fingers> Uncle John's Band> Drums> Two Soldiers Jam> Morning Dew> Turn On Your Lovelight; E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: My First This show rocks!!  Eddie Brickel opened and it rained.  Lightning was flying around the stage!! Frankly the show was so spooky I got lost and left early.  Amazing concert!!!! Life changing!!!  I'll never forget how funny I thought the sight of hippies with no shoes calling out cold imports was.  Little did I know that soon I'd be one of them!!!  Brent and Jery really shine with great support from the rest of the boys!!

rain? lighting? I think you were at a different show.

I was there at the spectrum.... and no rain, lighting, or eddie brickell. 

shows were mediocre too.
Lazy Lightning hard to have lightning in an indoor show.

da hell I' guessing mr.jakeggs acid trip was really crazy that night. i did not see eddie at the show however i did see a good show but nothing to write home about except its always nice to hear they love each other.

This show was really really hot I don't get the low ratings.  Very jammy, great Dew, UJB.  Oh, and it's Handsome Cabin Boy out of Space, not Two Soldiers.
I haven't listened to this source, but will give 5* to counteract all these other ratings, which are WAY too low, imo

Althea Good stuff. Jam at the end of Althea is sweet. Jerry had the whole place gasping for air while he was performing his magic. high time, playin>ujb> playin had me really confused at the show. I was like didn't i already hear this? Dosed and in the drivers seat. My 1st show w/ a dew, and my next 3 shows all had dews too. Spectrum rocks and was home base.

The Best Show I Never Saw I had a life changing experience this night. 

Left my house solo to see the show, drinkin and dosin and residual buzz from the night before's show. I blacked out half way there. Woke up sleeping on the streets of Philly near City Hall. Found my way to a cab. The guy wound up just letting me out and not asking for full pay,  I was so incoherent. I got in for the second set but was too messed up to dance. 

I was watching this great set but couldn't enjoy it.
It meant a lot to me to realize that if i couldn't drink and see the dead then i better stop driniking because I really liked the dead !
A week later I had my last drink, last drugs.

Went on to see about 20 more shows with a Wharf Rat mentallity and really enjoyed it. 
17 years after gettin the new start - I'm still livin the life I should.
